    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-hake-and-veg-parcel-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop into strips</p><p>Wash your <strong>pak choi</strong>, and pat it dry with kitchen paper, then cut the <strong>pak choi </strong>in half, separating the <strong>white bases</strong> and <strong>green tops</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>white bases</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-hake-and-veg-parcel-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-hake-and-veg-parcel-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>creamed</strong> <strong>coconut</strong> roughly (if required!) and dissolve it in 100ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [150ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span><span class=\"text-purple\"> </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>Thai green curry paste</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> chopped ginger</strong>, 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> and your <strong>lemongrass &</strong> <strong>lime leaf paste </strong>and stir it all up \u2013 this is your <strong>Thai-style curry stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-hake-and-veg-parcel-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut A3 size sheets of <strong>baking paper</strong> (or tin foil)</p><p>Divide the<strong> pepper</strong> <strong>strips </strong>and the<strong> pak choi green tops </strong>and <strong>chopped white bases </strong>evenly between the sheets</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-hake-and-veg-parcel-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Lay each <strong>hake fillet </strong>on top of the vegetables and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-hake-and-veg-parcel-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slightly scrunch the edges of the paper around the filling and then add the <strong>Thai-style curry stock </strong>evenly between each parcel</p><p>Scrunch the edges of the <strong>baking paper</strong> around the fish to form a sealed parcel and add to a baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 17 min or until the fish is cooked through and the veg has softened \u2013 this is your <strong>Thai-style hake & veg</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-hake-and-veg-parcel-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> Thai-style hake & veg </strong>with the <strong>basmati rice</strong> to the side</p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, press the rice into small bowls and turn out</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
